%N A061606 Ooguri-Vafa invariants of disk domain wall degeneracies for brane I in the O(K) -> P^1 X P^1 geometry.
%C A061606 This is row k[s] = 4 in Table 1, "m = 1", of the Aganagic-Klemm-Vafa paper (page 20) and preprint (page 38); due to formula (6.9) also the opposite of row k[s] = 4 in Table 2, "m = -1", up to the offset/leading 0. - _M. F. Hasler_, Nov 03 2025
%C A061606 Values are derived from Fang-Liu (Comm. Math. Phys. 323 (2013), Section 6.3, framing f=-1) via the mirror map, matching AKV Table 1; closed form follows from LLLZ rationality and finite-difference rigidity. - _Steven Kotlarz_, Mar 31 2026
%H A061606 Steven Kotlarz, <a href="/A061606/b061606.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200</a>
%H A061606 Mina Aganagic, Albrecht Klemm, and Cumrun Vafa, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1515/zna-2002-1-201">Disk Instantons, Mirror Symmetry and the Duality Web</a>, Z. Naturforsch. A 57 (2002), 1-28; also <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/0105045">arXiv:hep-th/0105045</a>, 2001.
%H A061606 B. Fang and C.-C. M. Liu, <a href="https://doi.org/10.48550/arXiv.1103.0693">Open Gromov-Witten Invariants of Toric Calabi-Yau 3-Folds</a>, Comm. Math. Phys. 323 (2013), 285-328.
%H A061606 Steven Kotlarz, <a href="/A061606/a061606_3.md.txt">Proof of Formula</a>
%H A061606 Steven Kotlarz, <a href="/A061606/a061606_4.md.txt">Fang-Liu Bridge</a>
%F A061606 a(n) = (n+1) * Sum_{k=0..4} h(k) * binomial(n-k+12, 12), where h = (1, 22, 67, 22, 1). - _Steven Kotlarz_, Mar 16 2026
%o A061606 (Python)
%o A061606 from math import comb
%o A061606 def a(n):
%o A061606     h = [1, 22, 67, 22, 1]
%o A061606     return (n+1) * sum(h[k] * comb(n-k+12, 12) for k in range(5))
%o A061606 # _Steven Kotlarz_, Mar 16 2026
%o A061606 (PARI) a(n) = {my(h=[1,22,67,22,1]); (n+1)*sum(k=0,4,h[k+1]*binomial(n-k+12,12))} \\ _Steven Kotlarz_, Mar 16 2026
